<p>As in topic. I tried to do this with standard HttpURLConnection, </p>  <pre><code>setRequestProperty("Authorization", "Basic" + authorization()); </code></pre>  <p>where</p>  <pre><code>public String authorization() {         String credentials = auth.getUser() + ":" + auth.getPassword();         String encoding = new sun.misc.BASE64Encoder().encode(credentials.getBytes());          return encoding;     } </code></pre>  <p>but it doesnt work. getRequestProperty("Authorization") gives null</p>  <p>Google images are downloaded without any problem. Have you got any idea on how to do this? </p>  <h1><strong>SOLUTION:</strong></h1>  <p><strong><a href="http://www.mkyong.com/java/how-to-automate-login-a-website-java-example/" rel="nofollow">mykong's post</a></strong></p>